header.gameNote: STATE FARM GOOD NEIGHBOR CLASSIC AT EL PASO TX

article.headline: Colgate 64, Miss. Valley St. 53
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Alvin Reed scored 13 points to lead Colgate to a 64-53 victory over winless Mississippi Valley State in the Sun Bowl tournament consolation game Wednesday night. Colgate (6-7), which lost to Georgetown in the semifinals Tuesday, led Mississippi Valley State 27-22 at halftime and never trailed in the second half. Jeffrey Price had 11 points and a game-high 12 rebounds for Mississippi Valley State (0-9), which shot just 26.7 percent from the field. Mike Thomas had 14 points. Mississippi Valley State pulled within a point with 11:58 remaining, but Colgate responded with a 13-2 spurt, including seven points from Kyle Roemer. Roemer and Dan Gentile scored nine apiece for Colgate.
